9 "(c) Information Sharing. – The assigned escalation specialist shall coordinate with the county
10 department of social services to obtain access to the entirety of each case record for a high-risk
11 home to address immediate safety of the juvenile. Upon request, the county department of social
12 services shall provide any records in their possession related to the high-risk home in which the
13 juvenile is placed, including the juvenile's case, and identified in the escalation notification form.
14 Pursuant to G.S. 7B-302, the escalation specialist may also demand, in writing, records in
15 possession of State or local law enforcement.";
